# Documentation Index

## Structure

**`ai-docs/`** - Main documentation directory:
- **`ai-design/`** - Phase 2 design docs
- **`ai-plans/`** - Phase 3 implementation plans
- **`ai-implementation/`** - Phase 5 implementation docs
- **`ai-learnings/`** - Project patterns and lessons learned
- **`features/`** - Feature documentation
- **`docs/`** - User-facing operational docs (top level)

**`.cursor/rules/`** - AI agent rules

## Usage

- **Phase 1 (Understand)**: Read existing docs in `ai-docs/`.
- **Phase 2 (Design)**: Create new doc in `ai-docs/ai-design/`.
- **Phase 3 (Plan)**: Create new doc in `ai-docs/ai-plans/`.
- **Phase 5 (Document)**: Create new doc in `ai-docs/ai-implementation/`.
- **Phase 6 (Update)**: Update `ai-docs/features/`, `docs/`, and `ai-docs/ai-learnings/`.

Always keep this index and the `ai-learnings` up to date when patterns change.
